      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A weak race and with plenty of rain forecast it will be a slog. MONTEVECCHIO (2) was outgraded on a good surface at Ipswich but his soft track form prior was promising. Steps up 220m on a 7-day return and he's the one to beat on form. COOLOUNDRA (4) is in a smart local barn and steps up from a plain effort here over 1800m on a heavy track. If he goes around he's worth another chance and third-up over a staying distance should suit better. Wary. PREACHABULL (6) flopped at Ipswich along with the top selection. His efforts leading into that are less encouraging but he should be around the mark. RUBOS (3) maybe next.",
